# BROWSER-notifications.md - Substack Notification & Reply Detection Patterns

## SS 1. Extract Notifications

Page: `https://substack.com/activity` (embed 3s wait in evaluate)

Substack calls notifications "Activity". Tabs: All, Replies, Restacks. Only process "Replies" tab items.

🚨 **Dedup key = URL + text snippet.** Substack does NOT expose unique per-comment URLs on the activity page. Multiple replies on the same thread share the same note URL. The `snippet` field (first 30 chars of reply body) distinguishes them.

🚨 **"Replied to your note" notifications have NO post URL in the DOM** — only the author profile link. When a notification has `isReply=true` but no `/note/` or `/p/` link, the agent must click the row to discover the URL, then navigate back to `/activity` before continuing extraction. See Step 2 below.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    // Click "Replies" tab to filter to actionable items
    var tabs = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var repliesTab = tabs.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Replies');
    if (repliesTab) {
      repliesTab.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true }));
      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
    }

    // Check for empty state
    if (document.body.innerText.includes("don't have any activity")) {
      return { count: 0, items: [], empty: true };
    }

    // Extract notification rows — linkRow contains nested linkRows, so dedup by URL+snippet
    var rows = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll("[class*='linkRow']"));
    var seen = new Set();
    var items = [];
    for (var row of rows) {
      var text = row.innerText || '';
      var isReply = /replied|commented|response/i.test(text);
      if (!isReply) continue;
      var author = text.split('\\n')[0] || '';
      if (/{{name}}|{{handle}}/i.test(author)) continue;
      var link = Array.from(row.querySelectorAll('a[href]')).find(a => {
        var h = a.href || '';
        return h.includes('/note/') || h.includes('/p/') || h.includes('/comment/');
      });
      if (!link) continue;
      var url = link.href.split('?')[0];
      // Extract reply body snippet — find first line >20 chars that is NOT the "replied to..." header
      var lines = text.split('\\n').filter(l => l.trim());
      var snippet = '';
      for (var i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
        var line = lines[i].trim();
        if (line.length > 20 && !/replied|commented|liked|your comment on/i.test(line) && !/^\\d+[hmd]$/.test(line)) {
          snippet = line.slice(0, 30);
          break;
        }
      }
      // Dedup by URL + snippet (same URL can have multiple replies with different snippets)
      var key = url + '|' + snippet;
      if (seen.has(key)) continue;
      seen.add(key);
      items.push({
        type: 'reply',
        author: author.slice(0, 40),
        postUrl: url,
        snippet: snippet,
        rowIndex: Array.from(document.querySelectorAll("[class*='linkRow']")).indexOf(row),
        needsClick: !url
      });
      if (items.length >= 10) break;
    }
    return { count: items.length, items };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

