## SS 1b. Resolve Missing URLs (for "replied to your note" notifications)

🚨 **Only needed for items where `needsClick: true`** (no `/note/` or `/p/` link found in DOM).

For each item with `needsClick: true`:
1. Click the notification row by index to navigate to the note
2. Read `window.location.href` — this gives the note URL (e.g. `/@author/note/c-XXXXXXX`)
3. Navigate back to `https://substack.com/activity` and re-click "Replies" tab
4. Store the discovered URL in the item's `postUrl`

```javascript
// Step 1: Click the row to discover URL
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    var rows = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll("[class*='linkRow']"));
    var targetRow = rows[${rowIndex}];
    if (!targetRow) return { error: 'row not found at index ${rowIndex}' };
    var clickable = targetRow.querySelector("[class*='isClickable']") || targetRow;
    clickable.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    return { url: window.location.href };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

After getting the URL, navigate back: `browser.navigate("https://substack.com/activity")`, wait 3s, click "Replies" tab again.

🚨 **Do this BEFORE the grep pre-check** — items need URLs for dedup to work.

